text: >Here are the essential details. Opening at 811 SE Stark, Danwei Canting will be 2000 square feet, seating 49 inside, with three or four tables outdoors. It'll have a fast-casual vibe and offer counter service, and once up and running, it will serve lunch and dinner. For drinks, find local and Chinese beers on tap; baijou cocktails with help from Portland's Vinn Distillery, which makes baijou; and a few other cocktails.

attachments.title: Turkey and Zucchini Burgers with Green Onion and Cumin - The View from Great Island
attachments.text: I can’t resist a burger that’s packed with greens, whether it’s green veggies, leafy greens, or fresh herbs, it doesn’t matter, greens mixed in with the meat make burgers extra tender, juicy and bursting with flavor.  These turkey burgers get their green personality from grated zucchini, green onions, mint and cilantro.  They’re browned in a skillet and then finished off in the oven, which gives them great caramelization on the outside and  helps insure that they aren’t tough inside.  With their spring green color, almost meatball-like texture, and  subtle Middle Eastern spicing, these patties are worlds away from [...]
